data.current_description: Private Preview. This feature is only available for approved services. This method provides admission control for services that are integrated with [Service Infrastructure](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure). It checks whether an operation should be allowed based on the service configuration and relevant policies. It must be called before the operation is executed. For more information, see [Admission Control](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/admission-control). NOTE: The admission control has an expected policy propagation delay of 60s. The caller **must** not depend on the most recent policy changes. NOTE: The admission control has a hard limit of 1 referenced resources per call. If an operation refers to more than 1 resources, the caller must call the Check method multiple times. This method requires the `servicemanagement.services.check` permission on the specified service. For more information, see [Service Control API Access Control](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/service-control/access-control).
data.summary_suggestion: Check if operation is allowed by service policies
data.description_suggestion: Performs admission control for service operations by evaluating whether an operation should be allowed based on service configuration and policies. Must be called before operation execution. Accepts a CheckRequest containing operation details and returns a CheckResponse indicating approval status. Supports maximum 1 referenced resource per call; multiple calls required for operations referencing more resources. Note: Policy propagation has ~60s delay; do not rely on most recent policy changes. Requires servicemanagement.services.check permission.
data.reasoning: Missing summary entirely. Description is verbose and mixes implementation details with operational guidance. Improved summary provides clear action-oriented statement. data.current_description: Private Preview. This feature is only available for approved services. This method provides telemetry reporting for services that are integrated with [Service Infrastructure](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure). It reports a list of operations that have occurred on a service. It must be called after the operations have been executed. For more information, see [Telemetry Reporting](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/telemetry-reporting). NOTE: The telemetry reporting has a hard limit of 1000 operations and 1MB per Report call. It is recommended to have no more than 100 operations per call. This method requires the `servicemanagement.services.report` permission on the specified service. For more information, see [Service Control API Access Control](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/service-control/access-control).
data.summary_suggestion: Report executed service operations for telemetry
data.description_suggestion: Reports telemetry data for operations executed on a service. Must be called after operations have completed. Accepts a ReportRequest containing a list of operations and returns a ReportResponse. Supports maximum 1000 operations and 1MB per call; recommended limit is 100 operations per call for optimal performance. Enables Service Infrastructure to track and analyze service activity. Requires servicemanagement.services.report permission.
data.reasoning: Missing summary entirely. Description is verbose with mixed implementation details. Improved summary provides clear action-oriented statement indicating telemetry reporting purpose. Improved description specifies inputs (ReportRequest with operation list), outputs (ReportResponse), operational constraints (1000 ops/1MB hard limit, 100 ops recommended), and required permissions while using consistent Service Infrastructure terminology.

data.current_description: Private Preview. This feature is only available for approved services. This method provides admission control for services that are integrated with [Service Infrastructure](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure). It checks whether an operation should be allowed based on the service configuration and relevant policies. It must be called before the operation is executed. For more information, see [Admission Control](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/admission-control). NOTE: The admission control has an expected policy propagation delay of 60s. The caller **must** not depend on the most recent policy changes. NOTE: The admission control has a hard limit of 1 referenced resources per call. If an operation refers to more than 1 resources, the caller must call the Check method multiple times. This method requires the `servicemanagement.services.check` permission on the specified service. For more information, see [Service Control API Access Control](https://cloud.google.com/service-infrastructure/docs/service-control/access-control).
